    "The CVC-ClinicVideoDB database is the first video-annotated database that is publicly available, introduced by Bernal et al. (2012).",
    "There are 15 separate standard-definition 7 Page 30 of 53 (SD) video sequences illustrating a polyp.",
    "The sequences were captured using OLYMPUS QF190 endoscopes and an Exera III video-grabber.",
    "There are 10924 frames in CVC-Clin-icVideoDB, each measuring 768 × 576, of which 9221 have a polyp.",
    "For each frame, the ground truth corresponds to a binary image in which white pixels represent all pixels in the image."
